
<manpage TITLE="auth2" SECTNUM=8>
<sect1>NAME 
 <P>auth2 - authentication server



<sect1>SYNOPSIS<P>
<bf>auth2</bf> &lsqb;-r&rsqb; &lsqb;-chk&rsqb; &lsqb;-x debuglevel&rsqb; &lsqb;-p pwfile&rsqb; &lsqb;-tk tokenkey&rsqb; &lsqb;-fk filekey&rsqb;<P>


<sect1>DESCRIPTION<P>
<bf>auth2</bf> is the Coda authentication server.  Clients need to have an
authentication token from <bf>auth2</bf> in order to establish
authenticated connections to Coda file servers.

<bf>auth2</bf> supports the following commands line options:
<descrip>
<tag><bf>-r</bf></tag>Tells <bf>auth2</bf> to print log entries to
the controlling tty rather than a log file.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-chk</bf></tag>Causes <bf>auth2</bf> to only validate
passwords.  New password entries cannot be added via this server
instance.  Servers started with the <bf>-chk</bf> option are slave servers.
There should only be one master server in the system.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-x</bf> <em>debuglevel</em></tag>Sets the server debug
level.  This level control the amount of debugging information printed
by the server.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-p</bf> <em>pwfile</em></tag>Used to tell <bf>auth2</bf> where
its password file is.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-tk</bf> <em>tokenkey</em></tag>Specifies where the token
key file <bf>auth2</bf> should use when encrypting tokens.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>-fk</bf> <em>filekey</em></tag>Name of file containing the key
decrypt password file with.
<P></descrip>


